    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <head>No. 503.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">de
                                    Zamacona</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-06-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 27,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 24th ultimo, relative to the raids into
                            Mexico from the United States by certain reservation Indians who were
                            granted permission to go in search of some of their missing tribe.</p>
                <p>A copy of your note has been communicated for the information of the
                            Secretary of the Interior, who has been asked to adopt all proper and
                            needful precautions against similar recurrences.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
